\u1780\\u1798\\u17d2\\u1796\\u17bb\\u1787\\u17b6\\r\\n\\u1793\\u17b7\\u1784\\u1798\\u1787\\u17d2\\u1788\\u178f\\u17d2\\u178f\\u1780\\u17b6\\u179a\\u1796\\u17b6\\u178e\\u17b7\\u1787\\u17d2\\u1787\\u1780\\u1798\\u17d2\\u1798\\u1780\\u1798\\u17d2\\u1796\\u17bb\\u1787\\u17b6\\r\\n\\u1796\\u17d2\\u179a\\u1798\\u1791\\u17b6\\u17c6\\u1784\\u179c\\u17b7\\u1792\\u17b6\\u1793\\u1785\\u17d2\\u1794\\u17b6\\u1794\\u17cb\\u1780\\u1798\\u17d2\\u1796\\u17bb\\u1787\\u17b6\\r\\n\\u178a\\u17be\\u1798\\u17d2\\u1794\\u17b8\\u1792\\u17d2\\u179c\\u17be\\u1787\\u17b6\\u1798\\u17bc\\u179b\\u178a\\u17d2\\u178b\\u17b6\\u1793\\u1780\\u17d2\\u1793\\u17bb\\u1784\\u1780\\u17b6\\u179a\\u178a\\u17c4\\u17c7\\u179f\\u17d2\\u179a\\u17b6\\u1799\\u179c\\u17b7\\u179c\\u17b6\\u1791\\u178a\\u17c2\\u179b\\u17a2\\u17b6\\u1785\\u1780\\u17be\\u178f\\u1798\\u17b6\\u1793<\\/span><\\/font><br \\/>\\r\\n<font face=\\\"Arial\\\"><span lang=\\\"hi-in\\\" xml:lang=\\\"hi-in\\\">\\u17a1\\u17be\\u1784\\u17d4\\r\\n<\\/span><\\/font>\\r\\n<\\/p>\\r\\n<p><strong>(Foreign member)<\\/strong> \\r\\n<\\/p>\\r\\n<p>1. Khmer is the official language in ATOMY (CAMBODIA) Co., Ltd.\\r\\nand English is the official language for foreign members. \\r\\n<\\/p>\\r\\n<p>2. The Member shall promote and sell Atomy products to ultimate\\r\\nconsumers and not sell or display those products in retail sales or\\r\\nservice establishments. The Member shall maintain the highest\\r\\nstandards of integrity, honesty, and responsibility in dealing with\\r\\nthe Company, consumers, and other members. \\r\\n<\\/p>\\r\\n<p>3. The Member shall present Atomy products in a truthful and\\r\\nsincere manner and keep the Company unharmed from damages resulting\\r\\nfrom misrepresentations by the Member. The Member shall protect the\\r\\nAtomy trademarks and trade name and obtain the Company\'s written\\r\\npermission prior to use in any advertising (including, but not\\r\\nlimited to, the Internet, literatures other than Company-published,\\r\\nlogos, pictures, and other marketing promotional devices). The Member\\r\\nunderstands that display or sale of Atomy products in public, retail\\r\\nor service establishments of any kind is inconsistent with the terms\\r\\nand conditions of this Agreement. \\r\\n<\\/p>\\r\\n<p>4. The Member and the Company agree that ordering Atomy products\\r\\nby website www.atomy.com\\/kh is the way to buy Atomy products from the\\r\\nCompany, and only Atomy members can log in to order. All orders\\r\\nsubmitted to the Company shall be accompanied by a credit card, debit\\r\\ncard, or such other methods as may be accepted by the Company. The\\r\\nMember understands that all orders are subject to acceptance by the\\r\\nCompany and the terms and conditions of this Agreement. \\r\\n<\\/p>\\r\\n<p>5. The Member is not a joint venture with, or franchisee, partner,\\r\\nagent or employee of the Company. The Member has no power or\\r\\nauthority to incur any debt, obligation or liability on behalf of the\\r\\nCompany. \\r\\n<\\/p>\\r\\n<p>6. The Member, as a self-employed and independent contractor, will\\r\\nbe operating his\\/her own business, making individual decisions and\\r\\nbuying and selling products available through the Company in his\\/her\\r\\nown account. The Company shall bear no legal responsibility for the\\r\\nactions taken by the Member. Furthermore, both Parties acknowledge\\r\\nthat the Member is not an employee of the Company and will not be\\r\\ntreated as an employee with respect to his\\/her Agreement for local\\r\\ntax purposes, or otherwise. \\r\\n<\\/p>\\r\\n<p>7. The Member shall be responsible for payment of any\\r\\nself-employment and other income taxes required by the Cambodian\\r\\ncompetent authorities, in compliance with law on taxation and\\r\\nrelevant regulation in force. \\r\\n<\\/p>\\r\\n<p>8. The Company may change suggested retail prices, discounts,\\r\\ncommissions, transportation charges, contest rules and active status\\r\\nrequirements at any time. The Company will give the Member at least\\r\\nfifteen (15) days\' prior notice of:<br \\/>\\r\\na) Changes to contest rules\\r\\nand active status requirements.<br \\/>\\r\\nb) Changes to suggested retail\\r\\nprices and shipping charges.<br \\/>\\r\\nc) Changes in standard discount and\\r\\ncommission schedules.<br \\/>\\r\\nWritten notice may be given by posting\\r\\nnotice on the Company\'s website. The Company or the Member may\\r\\nterminate this Agreement at any time and for any reason by giving\\r\\nthirty (30) days prior written notice to the other Party, or without\\r\\nprior notice and with immediate effect as a result of breach of any\\r\\nof the provisions of this Agreement herein. In determining what\\r\\nactions to be taken in the event of breach of this Agreement, the\\r\\nCompany may consider without limitation the nature and severity of\\r\\nthe breach. If the Member does not agree with any action taken by the\\r\\nCompany, the Member may submit dispute to appeal the decision with\\r\\nsupporting evidence during seven (7) days after the Company\\u2019s\\r\\naction or decision is taken. \\r\\n<\\/p>\\r\\n<p>9. The Member agrees to submit any dispute he\\/she may have to the\\r\\nCambodian Arbitration (National Commercial Arbitration Center or\\r\\n\\u201cNCAC\\u201d). The arbitration award shall be final and binding.\\r\\nCambodian Arbitration Rules shall govern the interpretation and\\r\\nproceedings of the arbitration. The Parties intend for the Dispute\\r\\nResolution Procedures to apply to the maximum degree possible in any\\r\\narbitration. If the Member becomes involved in a claim or dispute,\\r\\nthe Member will not disclose any matter that is subject to the\\r\\ndispute resolution process to any other person not directly involved\\r\\nin the conciliation or arbitration process. \\r\\n<\\/p>\\r\\n<p><strong>I. Atomy Salesman Code of Ethics<\\/strong><br \\/>\\r\\nThe Parties\\r\\nacknowledge that in order to establish respectful business culture\\r\\nand ensure fair and honest business activities among the members of\\r\\nATOMY (CAMBODIA) Co., Ltd. set forth the Code of Ethics and hereby\\r\\nrequest all its members to follow the Code of Ethics. All members\\r\\nshall comply with the Code of Ethics. This is a necessary process to\\r\\nprevent any unwanted disadvantages and encourage long-term growth of\\r\\nbusiness based on mutual trust between its members. Hence, there will\\r\\nbe strict enforcement of penalty in violation of the Code of Ethics,\\r\\ndepending on severity of breach of the Code of Ethics by the members.\\r\\n<\\/p>\\r\\n<p>1. The Parties agree that registering a person without his\\/her\\r\\nconsent, false information, or duplicates for one person and\\/or\\r\\nspouses being registered together is against the Company\\u2019s\\r\\nmembership registration rules. Memberships will be terminated\\r\\nimmediately upon confirmation. For any member who violates the\\r\\nmembership rules, his\\/her name will be immediately cancelled and\\r\\nhe\\/she will be penalized through cancellation of name, cancellation\\r\\nof name in line, postponing of commission fees, dropping of position,\\r\\nand moving toward the down-line following the decision of the Ethic\\r\\nEvaluation Commission after receiving the accurate certification. \\r\\n<\\/p>\\r\\n<p>2. The Member is forbidden from misleading other people by\\r\\nproviding false or exaggerated information about the Company. The\\r\\nMember understands that all members shall not mislead anyone with\\r\\nfalse information regarding the Company products, marketing plan, or\\r\\nfinancial rewards (i.e. any representations other than the official\\r\\ninformation provided by the Company including, but not limited to\\r\\nthose entailing the Atomy brand, marketing plan, product quality, and\\r\\nprice). \\r\\n<\\/p>\\r\\n<p>3. It is understood that the Member is prohibited from forcing its\\r\\ndown-lines or consumers to purchase products, doing any sort of\\r\\nmonetary\\/materialistic dealings for the purpose of membership\\r\\nregistration or withdrawal, and engaging in unreasonable purchases or\\r\\nunwanted selling of products for reasons other than pure consumption\\r\\n(i.e. Mastership achievement). \\r\\n<\\/p>\\r\\n<p>4. The Company prohibits persuading a consumer to purchase the\\r\\nCompany\\u2019s products by relying on any influential person in the\\r\\nsociety or promising to provide other benefits for consideration on\\r\\nthe registration for the Company\\u2019s membership. A repeated use of\\r\\nforce on any person who does not want to use the products of Atomy to\\r\\nbuy the products and\\/or make registration or payments are also not\\r\\nallowed. \\r\\n<\\/p>\\r\\n<p>5. The Company strictly prohibits recruiting between lines and\\r\\nabnormal changes of Sponsors and\\/or affiliated centers, and any other\\r\\npersonal connection based dealings which destroy mutual trust between\\r\\nthe Company\\u2019s members. \\r\\n<\\/p>\\r\\n<p>6. The Company strictly prohibits the act of certifying by the\\r\\nMember in order to confuse other person that he\\/she is the staff of\\r\\nthe Company or monopolized seller of the Company\\u2019s products. All\\r\\nacts of introducing another person who is not a member of the Company\\r\\nto do any activity in the manner of the member and criticizing and\\r\\nslandering another member or the Company are considered violation on\\r\\nthe Code of Ethics. The Member shall not transfer, sell and receive\\r\\ncommission fees from a third party and introduce the business of\\r\\nAtomy for doing other businesses. \\r\\n<\\/p>\\r\\n<p>7. It is understood and acknowledged that the Member shall not\\r\\nobstruct the working process of the Company with exaggerated queries\\r\\nwhich are not acceptable. The Company prohibits using attacking\\r\\nwords, displaying violent behavior at Company events, causing\\r\\nconflict, organizing protests and requesting to penalize other\\r\\nmembers of the Company without providing any appropriate supported\\r\\ndocuments. \\r\\n<\\/p>\\r\\n<p>8. The Parties agree that the Member shall not provoke other\\r\\nmembers into separating their families due to the Company\\u2019s\\r\\noperating activities and shall not convince other members not to go\\r\\nhome. In the case that the Member commits polygamy and sets a bad\\r\\nexample to other members, the Company will cancel the name of the\\r\\nMember or enforce other appropriate penalties following the decision\\r\\nof the Ethics Evaluation Commission. \\r\\n<\\/p>\\r\\n<p>9. The Company strictly prohibits monetary or product dealings\\r\\nbetween the Company\\u2019s members which involve illicit use of credit\\r\\ncards or financial dealings. The Member shall not enter into\\r\\ntransactions that are unauthorized. \\r\\n<\\/p>\\r\\n<p>10. The Member is strictly forbidden to recommend other MLM\\r\\nbusinesses (Multi-level Marketing), advertise or sell the products to\\r\\nother members. If the Member is a Sales Master or of higher status,\\r\\nthe membership will immediately be terminated upon confirmation of\\r\\nsuch actions. \\r\\n<\\/p>\\r\\n<p>11. The Member must thoroughly protect the personal information of\\r\\nconsumers and\\/or keep confidential of their information collected\\r\\nthrough the Atomy business. The Member may not use, copy, store, or\\r\\ndisclose it to any third party without the individual\\u2019s consent. \\r\\n<\\/p>\\r\\n<p>12. The Parties agree that the Company does not allow sale of the\\r\\nAtomy\\u2019s products on the Member\\u2019s personal website. Using\\r\\ntrademark or trade name of the Company in the personal website or in\\r\\nother ways of doing any business without approval from the Company is\\r\\nalso prohibited.<br \\/>\\r\\na. The Company shall not allow any commercial\\r\\npublication of Atomy via all kind of publication networks including\\r\\nprinting commercial cards.<br \\/>\\r\\n- The Member shall not make a\\r\\npublication of the products or other information of the Company\\r\\nwithout any approval from the Company.<br \\/>\\r\\n-The Company does not\\r\\nallow making a publication of the catalog or the sale distribution by\\r\\nusing the trademark of Atomy.<br \\/>\\r\\n- The Member is not allowed to use\\r\\nthe trademark of Atomy in order to make an exhibition for sale by\\r\\nusing the trademark of Atomy.<br \\/>\\r\\nb. Prohibition to show and sell\\r\\nproducts of Atomy<br \\/>\\r\\n-The Member shall not make an exhibition or\\r\\nsale of products in a shop, at exhibition place, in an office, in a\\r\\nvehicle, or along a street. All supplies and other providing ways in\\r\\norder to make an exhibition or sale as above mentioned are\\r\\nprohibited.<br \\/>\\r\\n-All members of Atomy must individually purchase the\\r\\nproducts from the Company and do not sub-distribute it to sellers.<br \\/>\\r\\nc.\\r\\nProhibition to change products and packaging<br \\/>\\r\\n-All members shall\\r\\nsell real products to users without changing products or packaging in\\r\\norder to make fraudulence to other products.<br \\/>\\r\\n-The Member shall\\r\\nnot modify products quantities and make new wrong packaging for the\\r\\noriginal products.<br \\/>\\r\\n-All members shall not do business contrary\\r\\nto the marketing strategic plan as provided by the Company.<br \\/>\\r\\nd.\\r\\nProhibition to do activities via internet<br \\/>\\r\\n-The Member shall not\\r\\nbring trademark and trade name of the Company for using in the\\r\\nwebsite or internet selling shop which will make an error to the\\r\\nofficial website of the Atomy.<br \\/>\\r\\n-The Member shall not provide\\r\\nunclear information or insufficient information and exaggerated\\r\\nstatement of the Company without any certification from the\\r\\nCompany.<br \\/>\\r\\n-The Member shall not make a publication by using a\\r\\ntrademark and trade name of the Company via personal email without\\r\\napproval from the Company.<br \\/>\\r\\nIn case of receiving a report of any\\r\\nmember of the Company does not comply with using prohibited\\r\\ninformation, the Company will issue penalty to any personal\\r\\nwrongdoer, center, presenter, and partner based on the wrongful doing\\r\\nlevel. \\r\\n<\\/p>\\r\\n<p>13. Registration of Couple Membership:<br \\/>\\r\\nThe Parties\\r\\nacknowledge that individuals who are legally married as husband and\\r\\nwife may join Atomy as members under one membership, and each person\\r\\nmay choose to be either primary or a secondary member. Registration\\r\\nand withdrawal procedure for couple membership is the same as regular\\r\\nmembership. However, if primary member resigns from Atomy, secondary\\r\\nmember will be terminated automatically.<br \\/>\\r\\na. Commissions shall be\\r\\ndisbursed to only the primary member, and all tax related duty,\\r\\nincluding income tax report, also shall lie with the primary\\r\\nmember.<br \\/>\\r\\nb. The couple members can change primary and secondary\\r\\nmembership by submitting document to the Company.<br \\/>\\r\\nc. Legally\\r\\nmarried couples are regarded as one member, and must hold only one\\r\\nmembership number.<br \\/>\\r\\nd. Spouses or partners of a person shall be\\r\\nconsidered as mastership holders, only if they are registered under\\r\\ncouple membership.<br \\/>\\r\\ne. If and when two members become legally\\r\\nmarried couple, each may keep their membership only if both are at\\r\\nmasterships of auto sales masters or above before the marriage.\\r\\nOtherwise, both shall operate under one membership number.<br \\/>\\r\\nf.\\r\\nOnce confirmed, duplicate membership shall be subject to disciplinary\\r\\naction by the Ethics Board of the Company.<br \\/>\\r\\ng. Application for\\r\\nchanges regarding couple membership must be submitted using one\'s\\r\\nlegal name, and all information submitted must be true.<br \\/>\\r\\nh. If\\r\\ncouple members who hold masterships above the auto sales master level\\r\\nare registered under two different membership IDs (duplicate\\r\\nregistration) with the recent account registered within a year, both\\r\\nshall be subject to probation of commission between minimum a month\\r\\nto maximum 3 months or else exceeding one year in registration, both\\r\\nshall be subject to probation of commission between minimum 3 months\\r\\nto maximum 12 months. The latter membership ID may be terminated\\r\\naccording to the deliberation of the Ethics Advisory Board of the\\r\\nCompany, regardless of mastership.<br \\/>\\r\\ni. For duplicate couple\\r\\nmembers with masterships below the auto sales master level, members\\r\\nshall be subject to warning and termination of the latter ID.\\r\\nHowever, settlement may vary depending on each case.<br \\/>\\r\\nj. The\\r\\nCompany shall not pose any restriction using their spouse\'s name\\r\\nafter two (2) years of voluntary withdrawal. \\r\\n<\\/p>\\r\\n<p>14. Obeying Laws and Regulations:<br \\/>\\r\\nThe Member shall fully\\r\\nunderstand and follow the relevant laws relating to the Company\\r\\nbusiness, as well as the policies and principles. The above Code of\\r\\nEthics must be obeyed in order to protect the Company\\u2019s members\\u2019\\r\\nbusiness and for long-term growth of all parties involved. The\\r\\nCompany has the right to impose penalties on any member in violation\\r\\nof these Policies, Principles and Code of Ethics through suspension\\r\\nor termination of membership, depending on severity of violation. In\\r\\naddition, the Parties agree that all connections with the Company\\r\\nwill cease upon termination of membership, and the terminated Member\\r\\nmay not continue practice of business as Member of the Company. \\r\\n<\\/p>\\r\\n<p><strong>II. Penalty and Cancellation of Membership by the Ethic\\r\\nEvaluation Commission<\\/strong><br \\/>\\r\\nThe Company has an ethic\\r\\nevaluation commission for preventing other risks which may be arisen\\r\\nby a commitment of the Member who violates the principles and rules\\r\\nof the Company. The Ethic Evaluation Commission has right and power\\r\\nto penalize by issuance of the decision without any objections. \\r\\n<\\/p>\\r\\n<p>1. Ethic Evaluation Commission is composed of five (5) members \\r\\n<\\/p>\\r\\n<p>2. Procedure of issuing disciplines and penalizing of the Ethic\\r\\nEvaluation Commission<br \\/>\\r\\na. Receiving a complaint and evidence on\\r\\nthe violation of the Principles and Rules of the Company.<br \\/>\\r\\nb.\\r\\nRequesting to defendant to appear for answering and providing\\r\\nevidence in order to obtain verification.<br \\/>\\r\\nc. Conducting\\r\\ninvestigation.<br \\/>\\r\\nd. Informing defendant via message and email. The\\r\\nMember who is defendant may request for reducing punishment or\\r\\npenalty within seven (7) days from the date of issuance of the\\r\\ndecision by the Ethic Evaluation Commission. The Member shall\\r\\ncooperate with the Ethic Evaluation Commission in the process of\\r\\ninvestigation. The case in which the Member provokes obstacles in the\\r\\nprocess of investigation by the Ethic Evaluation Commission shall be\\r\\ndeemed the violation activity to the executive principles of the\\r\\nCompany. \\r\\n<\\/p>\\r\\n<p>3. Type of penalties limited by the Ethic Evaluation Commission<br \\/>\\r\\na.\\r\\nPermanent cancellation of membership<br \\/>\\r\\nb. Suspension of commission\\r\\nfees<br \\/>\\r\\nc. Suspension of membership within limited period<br \\/>\\r\\nd.\\r\\nSuspension of commission providing<br \\/>\\r\\nAny penalty being issued by\\r\\nthe Company may be applied for the Member individually, and in line\\r\\ngroup by wrongdoing level in compliance with a decision of the Ethic\\r\\nEvaluation Commission. For the Member who committed a minor mistake,\\r\\nthe Company will issue a warning letter and in case of two (2) times\\r\\nrepeated wrongdoing, the Company will penalize following the\\r\\nwrongdoing level. All members shall know clearly the Principles of\\r\\nthe Company through the training schedules of the center. \\r\\n<\\/p>\\r\\n<p>4. Suspension and termination of membership<br \\/>\\r\\na. Suspension of\\r\\nmembership shall be made immediately in case of serious violation to\\r\\nthe Principles of the Company (immediate notice to the wrongdoer). A\\r\\nsuspension of membership shall be made from the wrongdoer to the\\r\\npresenter of the top line at least within two (2) months and in the\\r\\nterm of suspension of his\\/her membership, the Member could not be\\r\\nallowed to do activities as Member, and could be imposed on by other\\r\\npenalties following the decision of the Ethic Evaluation Commission\\r\\nsuch as prohibition to purchase or sell the products, deregistration\\r\\nas Member, no accessing into the system, no allowing to entry into\\r\\nthe center, and in case of wrongdoing by the center, the reserved\\r\\nchair in the center shall be cancelled. Decision to suspend the\\r\\npresenter of leading line based on the absence of the appropriate and\\r\\naccurate training which is the main roles of the presenter.<br \\/>\\r\\nb.\\r\\nThe Member can leave from membership of the Company freely by\\r\\nrequesting the Company for cancellation of the Member\\u2019s name via\\r\\npersonal website of Atomy.<br \\/>\\r\\nc. The Member who is providing false\\r\\ninformation in the process of registration or causing risks to the\\r\\nCompany by making a wrong marketing, his\\/ her name shall be cancelled\\r\\nfrom the Company\\u2019s membership. \\r\\n<\\/p>\\r\\n<p style=\\\"line-height:100%;margin-bottom:0in;\\\"><br \\/>\\r\\n\\r\\n<\\/p>\"}', '2021-10-07 11:21:56', '2021-11-24 03:51:12');
